FOUR officials of the National Environment Management Council (NEMC) appeared before the Kisutu Resident Magistrate's Court in Dar es Salaam today facing eight charges including money laundering. They are Deusdedit Katwale, Magori Matiku, Obadia Machupa, all environmental officers at NEMC headquarters and Lydia Nyinondi, who is an Assistant Accountant. The charges against them includes conspiracy, forgery, submitting forged documents, causing loss to the council, abuse of office and money laundering. They denied the charges before Principal Resident Magistrate Huruma Shaidi. However, the case was adjourned to June 18, 2020. Investigations into the matter, according to the prosecution led by State Attorney Janeth Magoho, have been completed.